FuncDef:
The whitelist disable command disables the whitelist function.
The undo whitelist disable command restores the default configuration.
By default, the whitelist function is enabled.
ExtraInfo:
Usage Scenario
You can configure ACL rules to add packets that need to be preferentially sent to the whitelist as required.
Precautions
In VS mode, this command is supported only by the admin VS.
After the whitelist function is disabled, you can still configure a whitelist, but the configured whitelist does not take effect.
